    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-11T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-11T05:00:00-05:00" n="44"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/11908: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-11T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 11, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 11—10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>180. I am informed that a number of reserve officers and some reservists of the
                    Finnish Army have been called up for service beginning yesterday. Crews of
                    Finnish vessels at Petsamo have been ordered to return to their ships to stand
                    by. All Finnish submarines are now concentrated at Helsinki. A German tanker of
                    1,500 tons arrived off the harbor this morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
